  "notes": "Kxa (formerly Northern Khoisan) click language of Namibia and Botswana, in the standardized Dickens (1994) orthography, the best-documented San orthography. Four click places (dental ǀ, lateral ǁ, alveolar ǃ, palatal ǂ; no bilabial) combine with g-voiced, n-nasal, h-aspirated, glottal ʼ, x-velar and k-release accompaniments written as digraphs. The apostrophe ʼ and the typewriter apostrophe are orthographic equivalents. Left unencoded: the four-plus level tones (entirely unwritten), pharyngealized/strident vowels beyond aq/oq, and murmured-voice vowels; these set a high PER floor. The k-release click value is the least certain part of the map.",
  "iso639_3": "ktz",
